  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "QC Inspector",
  "description": "<p><strong>Your Company</strong></p>\n<p>We are a future forward advanced mechanical precision manufacturing company with an outstanding &amp; proven track record for innovation, agility, growth &amp; stability. We are poised for our next phase of growth in the semi-conductor, medical, oil &amp; gas, aerospace, automotive &amp; optics sectors. Our team is rapidly expanding to fill the next generation leadership roles &amp; advance our current operational capabilities.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Your Calling</strong></p>\n<p>· Perform regular quality assessment on all incoming materials from vendors, in-process fabrication as well as outgoing parts for shipping</p>\n<p>· Reject all products and materials that fail to meet quality expectations</p>\n<p>· Read mechanical drawings, plans and specifications to understand the requirements of product</p>\n<p>· Measure product dimensions and compare final product to the specifications</p>\n<p>· Maintain records of testing, information and various metrics e.g. number of defective products per day</p>\n<p>· Monitor the use of measuring equipment to ensure it is safe and well-maintained</p>\n<p>· Resolve quality-related issues in a timely manner</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Your Success Factors</strong></p>\n<p>· Minimum 2 years of experience as quality inspector</p>\n<p>· Minimum NTC certification in Precision/Mechanical Engineering or any other related fields</p>\n<p>· Able to read mechanical drawings/blueprints</p>\n<p>· Strong understanding of quality control standards and testing techniques</p>\n<p>· Great attention to detail</p>",
